cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC. 

The paper deals with head pose estimation and tracking using RGBD cameras, which is a computer vision problem, hence it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The paper also mentions the use of a robot for motion compensation, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) category. The proposed multi-scale convolutional neural network architecture indicates that the paper could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) categories. Finally, the medical application of the research suggests that it could also belong to the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) category.
